# Film Listing Components

When building or changing film listing UIs:

- `PeliculaCard` is a renderer for server-provided film data. Do not fetch film details client-side from the card.
- Previous-edition film cards stay non-clickable until a historical film detail route exists. In Vue templates, use `:linkable="false"` (boolean binding) rather than linking to the current-edition `pelicula_path`.
- When `:linkable="false"`, remove click affordances such as hover underlines or cursor/link behavior.
- Keep `PeliculaCard` payload expectations small: title, countries, genre, duration, image, showcase tag/name, and URL only when links are enabled or needed as a key.

Component-specific notes:

- `IconArrowDown` currently accepts a `className` prop and applies it to the inner SVG. Do not replace it with Vue `:class` unless the icon component API is refactored.
- Search/filter controls on Inertia pages should update URL params through Inertia navigation, preserving server-owned data and infinite-scroll state.
- Add/update Vitest coverage when changing clickable vs non-clickable card behavior.
